canBreathe() - Method in class net.minecraftforge.event.entity.living.LivingBreatheEvent
If the entity can breathe and LivingBreatheEvent.canRefillAir() returns true, their air value will be increased by LivingBreatheEvent.getRefillAirAmount().
If the entity can breathe and LivingBreatheEvent.canRefillAir() returns false, their air value will stay the same.
If the entity cannot breathe, their air value will be reduced by LivingBreatheEvent.getConsumeAirAmount().

ChunkDataEvent - Class in net.minecraftforge.event.level
ChunkDataEvent is fired when an event involving chunk data occurs.
If a method utilizes this
invalid reference 
Event
as its parameter, the method will receive every child event of this class.

ChunkDataEvent.data contains the NBTTagCompound containing the chunk data for this event.

All children of this event are fired on the MinecraftForge.EVENT_BUS.

ChunkDataEvent.Load - Class in net.minecraftforge.event.level
ChunkDataEvent.Load is fired when vanilla Minecraft attempts to load Chunk data.
This event is fired during chunk loading in
invalid reference 
ChunkSerializer#read(ServerLevel, PoiManager, ChunkPos, SerializableChunkData)
which means it is async, so be careful.
ChunkDataEvent.Save - Class in net.minecraftforge.event.level
ChunkDataEvent.Save is fired when vanilla Minecraft attempts to save Chunk data.
This event is fired during chunk saving in ChunkMap#save(ChunkAccess).

ChunkEvent.LightingCalculated - Class in net.minecraftforge.event.level
ChunkEvent.LightingCalculated is fired when MinecraftForge flags that lighting is correct in a chunk.
This event is fired during light propagation in ThreadedLevelLightEngine.CompletableFuture(), specifically upon setting the ChunkAccess isLightCorrect to true.

The game test for this event is lighting_event_test in net.minecraftforge.debug.chunk

This event is not
invalid reference 
Cancelable
.

This event does not have a result.
